1 A BILL for an Act to create and enact a new section to chapter 15.1-18.2 and a new section to
2 chapter 50-06 of the North Dakota Century Code, relating to financial planning resources for
3 new teachers and onsite child care; and to provide for a legislative management study.
4 BE IT ENACTED BY THE LEGISLATIVE ASSEMBLY OF NORTH DAKOTA:
5 SECTION 1. A new section to chapter 15.1-18.2 of the North Dakota Century Code is
6 created and enacted as follows:
7 New teacher resource - Financial planning.
8 1. The teachers' fund for retirement board shall submit to the superintendent of public
9 instruction, in the manner prescribed by the superintendent of public instruction ,
10 resources related to maximizing earning potential for teachers. The teachers' fund for
11 retirement board directly shall communicate with and distribute resources to its
12 members, teacher mentor programs, educator preparation programs, and school
13 district administrators to inform new and recently hired teachers.
14 2. The superintendent of public instruction shall compile the information under
15 subsection 1 into a report and distribute the report to the teacher preparation
16 programs ; administrators, including superintendents, business managers, and building
17 principals ; and school districts for the benefit of educating new and recently hired
18 teachers.
19 SECTION 2. A new section to chapter 50-06 of the North Dakota Century Code is created
20 and enacted as follows:
