1 Onsite child care in school settings - Rules .
2 1. A school district may provide child care services or allow child care providers to deliver
3 child care services in a building located on school premises .
4 2. The department, in cooperation with education stakeholders invited by the department,
5 shall review and revise rules under chapter 28 - 32 to implement this section by July 1 ,
6 2026.
7 SECTION 3. LEGISLATIVE MANAGEMENT STUDY - HEALTH INSURANCE POOL FOR
8 SCHOOL DISTRICT EMPLOYEES. During the 2025-26 interim, the legislative management
9 shall consider studying the feasibility of, impact of, and process for creating a health insurance
10 pool for school district employees. The study must include a cost-benefit analysis of
11 implementing a health insurance pool, a review of health insurance pool plan designs and
12 administrative structures, and a comparative analysis of similar approaches adopted by other
13 states for school district employees. The study also must include an analysis of the impact a
14 health insurance pool would have on teacher salaries and a review of compensation structures
15 that maximize lifetime earnings. The legislative management shall report its findings and
16 recommendations, together with any legislation required to implement the recommendations, to
17 the seventieth legislative assembly.
18 SECTION 4. LEGISLATIVE MANAGEMENT STUDY - TEACHER LICENSING AND
19 RECRUITMENT. During the 2025-26 interim, the legislative management shall consider
20 studying the feasibility of adopting the interstate teacher mobility compact, teacher licensure
21 reciprocity, and universal licensing to improve teacher recruitment. The study must include input
22 from representatives of the workforce development council. The legislative management shall
23 report its findings and recommendations, together with any legislation required to implement the
24 recommendations, to the seventieth legislative assembly.
